      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This addition to the papers of Alexandra Ripley, ca.
         1990-1994, ca. 75 items (5 Hollinger boxes) consists of
         research notes, outlines, printed materials, and autograph and
         typed copies of manuscripts, for Ripley's novel about North
         Carolina and the tobacco industry, 
         <title render="italic">From Fields of Gold,</title>and one
         electrostatic typescript copy of 
         <title render="italic">Scarlett.</title>Also present is a pen
         and ink drawing titled "Old Mill of Guilford."</p>
      </scopecontent>
